props.text: This module provides a foundational overview of psychology as a science and explores its diverse areas of study. We'll delve into the historical roots of psychology, examining key figures and schools of thought that have shaped the field. You'll learn about the scientific method and how it's applied in psychological research to understand human behavior and mental processes. Additionally, we'll explore the biological influences on behavior, including the nervous system, brain structures, and genetics. Finally, we'll examine the various subfields within psychology, from clinical and counseling psychology to social and developmental psychology, giving you a taste of the diverse career paths available.

props.text:
By the end of this module, you will be able to:

  • Define psychology and explain its key goals.
  • Describe the historical development of psychology, including major schools of thought and influential figures.
  • Explain the scientific method and its application in psychological research.
  • Identify the biological bases of behavior, including the role of the nervous system, brain, and genetics.
  • Differentiate between the major subfields of psychology and identify potential career paths.

By the end of this module, you will be able to answer the following questions:

  • What is psychology, and how is it relevant to our lives?
  • How has psychology evolved as a scientific discipline?
  • How do biological factors influence our thoughts, feelings, and behaviors?
  • What are the different ways psychologists study human behavior?
  • What are the major subfields of psychology, and what types of questions do they address?
